data.text:
The following settings in the onbase32.ini file are used by solutions that employ the Hyland Bar Code Recognition for OnBase software. Many of these settings are used to clarify the in-memory image of a bar code page so that the results of the bar code process are improved.

These settings do not have any effect on the image of the bar code page stored on disk; all enhancements to the image as a result of these settings are done in-memory only.
